Such a bizarre release. Apart from the fact that it's an all-MGM compilation featuring the Looney Tunes characters on the cover, this second volume of MGM Cartoon Magic never saw a U.S. release.

Daffy Superstar

1990

Univideo, distributed by Panarecord

Hollywood Daffy - Book Review - Yankee Doodle Daffy

Slightly Daffy

More interesting about these Videomatto releases is a group image on the back covers showing the other characters Univideo releases under the label, all licensed from (at the time) various companies. The Popeye cartoons Univideo would release were from the King Features-owned package of 1960s shorts and episodes of Popeye and Son. Ironically, in the age of DVD all of the properties pictured (with the sole exception of the Pink Panther) would be handled by Warner Home Video.

As of this update, there is no evidence of a Porky Pig volume existing.
